FT  03 JUL 92 / World Stock Markets: Brazil
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Brazilian stocks rose 7 per cent by midday, continuing their recovery after
Monday's sharp losses on the political crisis over government corruption
charges, but ended with a net gain of just 0.8 per cent.
Sentiment was helped by rumours that an agreement with creditor banks on
