FT  03 JUL 92 / Observer: Gnomes' homes
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Insider pub just off Zurich's Paradeplatz is about to see its last
gathering of gnomes. This weekend the city's Bourse, Switzerland's
pre-eminent stock exchange, is moving to new premises a few hundred yards
away from the building it has occupied since 1930, which has the pub on its
ground floor.
But the gnomes' joy at escaping their cramped old quarters will be mixed
with bitterness about the long battle they've had to achieve the move. The
exchange's first application for a new-building permit was sent to the city
authority the whole of 14 years ago.
Worse, with change to electronic trading due within a year or so, the
spacious new trading floor will soon be redundant. And, to top it off, the
cantonal government that owns the building forbids tenants to fit air
conditioning in their offices.
Enter the summer of the steaming gnomes.
