<HEADLINE>
FT  03 JUL 92 / Parliament and Politics: Tory media man to quit
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MR Shaun Woodward, the Conservative party's director of communications, said
yesterday that he was to stand down. He said he had 'received offers' from
City firms and academic institutions but wanted to consider his options
before making a decision.
During the general election campaign he faced criticism over the Tory
effort, but yesterday won praise from Mr John Major and Sir Norman Fowler,
Tory party chairman.
