FT  03 JUL 92 / Parliament and Politics: Lilley pledge over pensions
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALISON SMITH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CHANGES to the pension age would not affect anyone expecting to retire in
the next few years, Mr Peter Lilley, social security secretary, emphasised
yesterday, Alison Smith writes.
With the consultation period on the equalisation of the state pension age
just ended, Mr Lilley said that no decisions had yet been taken, and that
all the 3,000-plus responses would be fully considered.
The expectation has been that a flexible decade of retirement has in effect
been ruled out, and that the costs of lowering the retirement age for men to
60 would be too great, leaving the raising of the retirement age for women
as the most likely option.
