<HEADLINE>
FT  03 JUL 92 / World Trade News: Davy wins Utah smelter contract
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW BAXTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Davy McKee, part of the engineering division of Trafalgar House, and Fluor
Daniel of the US have been awarded a contract for the engineering and
construction management of a new Dollars 600m (Pounds 324.3m) copper smelter
in Utah, writes Andrew Baxter. The client is Kennecott, owned by RTZ of the
UK, which is spending Dollars 880m on the new environmentally friendly
smelter and refinery at its Utah Copper operations near Salt Lake City.
Although Davy would not disclose its share of the 50/50 contract, the deal
is one of its biggest since the takeover last year by Trafalgar House and
one of Davy's biggest US contracts for some years.
</TEXT>
