<HEADLINE>
FT  03 JUL 92 / World Trade News: Argentina plans to boost car and truck
exports
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN BARHAM
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BUENOS AIRES
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ARGENTINA'S six car and truck manufacturers plan sharply to increase exports
to about Dollars 650m (Pounds 350m) a year and to invest Dollars 1.6bn over
the next three years as part of a mandatory investment and modernisation
plan, writes John Barham in Buenos Aires. Six months ago the government told
the companies it would relax import barriers under an export-oriented
policy. It told them to draw up investment plans showing how they would
adapt to liberalisation. Each company must run a positive trade balance by
1994 and cut its model range.
</TEXT>
