Total emoluments for Mr Hoffman, the highest paid director, fell from Pounds
209,000 to Pounds 199,000.
Thames also revealed it made a Pounds 50,000 contribution to the
Conservative Party as the board considered 'a Tory election win was in the
interests of the company and shareholders'.
