FT  03 JUL 92 / Christie's sell dinosaur egg for pounds 5,500
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CLIVE COOKSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Good egg: Christie's South Kensington yesterday sold a 70m-year-old
fossilised dinosaur egg for Pounds 5,500. The 18.2cm-long egg, which is
assumed to have come from a sauropod dinosaur Hypselosaurus, was found near
Aix-en-Provence, southern France, Clive Cookson writes.
Paleontologists have recovered hundreds of fossilised dinosaur eggs. Most
contain nothing but featureless stone when cracked open, but a few contain
remains of dinosaur embryos. If the new owner of the Hypselosaurus does not
want to risk the Pounds 5,500 investment by taking a hammer to the egg, it
would be possible to get an idea whether anything interesting is inside with
a specialised X-ray machine.
