<TEXT>
Moldova chose a new prime minister to grapple with its ethnic and economic
problems yesterday, amid renewed fighting between government forces and
separatists, Reuter reports from Kishinev. Mr Andrei Sangeli, approved by
185 out of 244 deputies in parliament, pledged to take emergency measures to
'stop the war against our country' and settle the dispute over the breakaway
Dnestr Republic by negotiation.
