<HEADLINE>
FT  02 JUL 92 / International Capital Markets: Greycoat loan refinanced
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TRACY CORRIGAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
GREYCOAT, the UK property company, has completed the refinancing of
Embankment Place, a central London office development, with a Pounds 125m
fixed-rate syndicated loan secured on the property. The loan was arranged by
Hypo-Bank and has been syndicated among German, Dutch and Swiss banks.
Earlier this year, Greycoat tried to refinance its Pounds 110m loan,
arranged in 1987 to finance the construction of the development, through a
Pounds 125m issue of 10-year discounted bonds. But the market was
unreceptive and the issue was cancelled.
Mr Richard Guignard, managing director (finance), said that when a
refinancing was first considered last year, rental income from the property
was not sufficient to service a bank loan. But, with lower interest rates,
annual net rental income of Pounds 15.3m now comfortably covers the annual
Pounds 13.7m refinancing cost.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
