<HEADLINE>
FT  02 JUL 92 / UK Company News: London Share Service
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Monday's list of forthcoming changes to company classifications in the
London Share Service should have stated that companies classified in Stock
Exchange category 98 will be shown with effect from July 4 under Investment
Trusts. The category includes investment trusts approved under Section 842
of the Income and Corporation Taxes Act but either registered outside the UK
or denominated, accounting or quoted in a foreign currency.
The placing of individual companies will be confirmed in the normal weekly
list of changes to the London Share Service.
</TEXT>
