FT  02 JUL 92 / Observer: Parsimoney
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Chris Haskins must surely be one of the lowest paid chairmen of a Footsie
company. Despite a 17 per cent pay rise last year, the cheery chairman of
Northern Foods was only paid Pounds 181,000.
Indeed, his entire seven-man board - which includes three non-executives -
